The Democratic Alliance (DA) on Monday laid criminal charges against Mineral Resources Minister, Mosebenzi Zwane, and the Gupta brothers - Atul Gupta, Ajay Gupta, Rajesh Gupta, as well as Ronica Ragavan and Kamal Vasram.The charges include:"This follows revelations that public funds, meant to assist the poor, were allegedly washed through a complex web of front companies, and used to pay for Vega Gupta and Aakash Jahajgarhia s wedding at Sun City in 2013," said David Maynier MP - the DA's Shadow Minister of Finance."I have also written to the South African Revenue Service requesting an investigation into tax evasion relating to allegations that wedding expenses were irregularly deducted as business expenses by Linkway Trading (Pty) Ltd, which is a South African based company controlled by the Guptas, consequently evading paying tax on an amount of about R30 million in 2014."Maynier said that the fact that public funds, meant to assist the poor, were allegedly used to pay for President Jacob Zuma s number one clients', the Guptas , family wedding is grotesque and must be investigated without fear or favour by the South African Police Service.